Create an empty folder
npm init to generate package.json
create the index.js in package.json which is the entry point of our application.
npm install express
run node index.js from the console
refactor code and install nodemon --save-dev
install body-parser
install cors morgan
install moongoose
create models folder

Created the angular project within the same project called client.

change package.json file in node project to
"scripts": {
    "start": "node index",
    "server": "nodemon index",
    "client-install": "npm install --prefix client",
    "client": "npm run start --prefix client",
    "dev": "concurrently \"npm run server\" \"npm run client\""
  },
and then run the command
npm install -D concurrently